subtasks.context_scope:
CONTRACT DEFINITION:
1. RESEARCH NOTE: getContextUsage() returns ContextUsage | undefined (VERIFIED). ContextUsage.tokens is nullable (null 'right after compaction, before next LLM response'). ctx.model has contextWindow: number and maxTokens: number (both required when model is defined). The input event fires BEFORE the turn, so tokens may be null/stale — this is the documented O-1 fallback. estimateTokens takes AgentMessage not a string (VERIFIED) — use the chars/4 heuristic (O-3). The read tool DEFAULT_MAX_LINES is 2000 (VERIFIED), confirming HEAD_BYTES=8192 ≈ 2000 lines. Existing test case #2 uses FIX = { cwd: TMPDIR } with NO getContextUsage — it hits the O-1 fallback (no budget → whole injection) and does NOT need to change. See architecture/system_context.md §3-4 and architecture/test_and_docs_analysis.md §1.7.
2. INPUT: The widened injectFiles from S1 with: the 5 constants, formatPagedDirectiveBlock, ctx type including optional getContextUsage() and model, return type including paged: number (currently always 0). The text/binary branch at L194-200, specifically L199 (currently: blocks.push(formatTextFileBlock(abs, buf.toString('utf8')))). Local state at L127-129 (blocks[], images, count=0).
3. LOGIC:
  a. Before the token loop (after L129 'let count = 0'), add:
     let paged = 0;
     Compute budget ONCE:
       const usage = ctx.getContextUsage?.();
       let remaining: number | null;
       if (usage === undefined || usage.tokens === null) { remaining = null; } // O-1 fallback: no paging
       else {
         const window = usage.contextWindow;
         const used = usage.tokens;
         const reserve = ctx.model?.maxTokens ?? DEFAULT_RESERVE;
         remaining = Math.max(0, window - used - reserve - MARGIN);
       }
     Declare a mutable copy for multi-file subtraction: let remainingBudget = remaining;
  b. At the text-file decision point (L199), replace the single formatTextFileBlock call with:
     const content = buf.toString('utf8');
     const fileCost = Math.ceil(content.length / 4); // O-3 heuristic
     if (remainingBudget === null || fileCost <= PAGED_THRESHOLD * remainingBudget) {
       // INLINE (whole) — current behavior preserved
       blocks.push(formatTextFileBlock(abs, content));
       if (remainingBudget !== null) remainingBudget = Math.max(0, remainingBudget - fileCost);
     } else {
       // PAGED — head block + directive (PRD §5.5 Page path)
       blocks.push(formatTextFileBlock(abs, content.slice(0, HEAD_BYTES)));
       blocks.push(formatPagedDirectiveBlock(abs, content.length));
       paged++;
       remainingBudget = Math.max(0, remainingBudget - Math.ceil(HEAD_BYTES / 4));
     }
  c. count++ at L202 is UNCHANGED — it counts ALL delivered files (whole and paged both count). This preserves the existing early-return guard 'if (count === 0)' semantics (PD-1 rule 3).
  d. Update both return sites to include the computed paged value:
     Early-return (L209): return { text, images: imagesIn, injected: 0, paged: 0 };
     Final-return (L217): return { text: finalText, images, injected: count, paged };
  e. Budget computation must live inside the existing per-file try/catch (or at minimum, never throw out of injectFiles — PRD §12.5). If ctx.getContextUsage throws, catch it and set remaining = null.
4. OUTPUT: injectFiles branches between inline (whole) and paged (head + directive) for text files based on a best-effort remaining-context budget. Returns { text, images, injected, paged }. Images, binaries, and missing/directory paths are UNCHANGED. Existing tests with FIX = { cwd } (no budget) hit the O-1 fallback → whole injection → pass without modification.
5. MOCKING: New paged-delivery tests need a mock ctx with getContextUsage() returning a tight budget (see architecture/system_context.md §4). Example: const PAGED_FIX = { cwd: TMPDIR, getContextUsage: () => ({ tokens: 10000, contextWindow: 50000, percent: 20 }), model: { contextWindow: 50000, maxTokens: 8192 } }. Under this budget, huge.log (~2MB, fileCost ~524K) gets PAGED; a.ts (~200 chars, fileCost ~50) gets WHOLE. Assert: paged > 0, text contains head block with first HEAD_BYTES, text contains directive block with abs path and instruction, injected count includes the paged file, final text stripped of #@, images unchanged for text files. Also test multi-file mixed (one small whole + one large paged), budget-unknown fallback (existing FIX → whole), and regression that images/binaries are unaffected.
6. DOCS: Mode A — none beyond S1's JSDoc update. The injectFiles JSDoc already describes paged delivery from S1.
